TONGA &#8211; Police arrested a 21-year-old man for possession of rhino horn in Block C, KaSiboshwa on Friday morning.The SAPS rushed to a house after receiving a tip-off. On arrival, while police were talking to the homeowner, they noticed a man in the backyard running with a black plastic bag. They gave chase and apprehended the suspect as he was making his way towards a nearby sugar-cane farm. Police investigations are still continuing.READ MORE: Hunting rifle hidden under vehicle by poaching suspects